INSERT INTO `webform_submitted_data` (`nid`,`sid`,`cid`,`no`,`data`) VALUES (10,28,19,'0','Tables used in the database: This will provide a short description of the information captured in individual tables in the database.\r\n\r\n1A Report Basics: Dates of application and acceptance, type of report, name of the sponsor, and general location of the proposed infrastructure.\r\n\r\n2A Contact Info: The contact information for individuals from the sponsor, consulting engineers, and other interested parties.\r\n\r\n2B Project Sponsor: Information about the entity that is applying for funds from the Board of Water Resources\r\n\r\n3A Existing Conditions: Conditions in the region of interest that are specified in the report such as population growth and development, a shortage of irrigation or drinking water, etc.\r\n\r\n3B Existing Problems: Specific problems that are cited in the report that can be addressed such as seepage occurring from canals, safety hazards associated with water infrastructure, or the need for expansion of the infrastructure.\r\n\r\n4A Existing Infrastructure: Water infrastructure that is already in place. This is not an exhaustive list, just a summary of the important parts of the current system.\r\n\r\n4B Proposed Infrastructure: Water infrastructure that will be built using the funding provided by the Board\r\n\r\n4C Infrastructure, Other: Other details about the existing and proposed infrastructure such as is the proposed infrastructure replacing an existing canal with a pipe, or if the proposed will be connecting to existing storage or pipes. Also captures, details about what purposes the system will be used for, whether agricultural, or residential.\r\n\r\n5A Cost Estimate: The estimated cost of the project broken down in to specific categories such as construction, easement acquisition, and engineering fees. \r\n\r\n5B Cost Sharing: The amount and proportion of the funding from which sources.\r\n\r\n5C Repayment: The terms of repayment by the sponsor to the Board\r\n\r\n6 Economic Feasibility: The benefits to individuals, the sponsor, and the area e predicted to result from the proposed infrastructure.\r\n\r\n7 Water Rights: Water rights held by involved parties that will be used by the proposed infrastructure.\r\n\r\n8A Easements: Whether easement or land purchases will be required to complete the infrastructure\r\n\r\n8B Enviro: The impact expected on the environment by the construction of the project, and whether environmental clearance is required in order to build the infrastructure.\r\n\r\n8C Conservation: How much water is predicted to be conserved by the new infrastructure, the use that conserved water will be put to, and any other information about conservation practices put in place by the sponsor.\r\n\r\n99 Withdrawal: This report is to notify the Board that a specific project has been cancelled and for what reason\r\n\r\n999 Additional Funds: Sponsors apply for additional funds from the Board above the original loan due to unexpectedly high costs to build the project\r\n\r\n9999 Committal of Funds: This report summarizes the project(a more detailed report has already been reviewed by the Board)and officially commits Board funds to the sponsor.\r\n');
