INSERT INTO `webform_submitted_data` (`nid`,`sid`,`cid`,`no`,`data`) VALUES (10,30,19,'0','Worksheet: all projects\r\n\r\nFields:\r\nApplNo: This is a unique identifier given to projects by Board staff when an application is submitted to the Board for funding.\r\n\r\nProj No: We are not sure where this number comes from, or what it is used for.\r\n\r\nSPONSOR: The name of the entity applying for funds. This can be a private company, water district, municipality, or individuals.\r\n\r\nFund: There are several funds controlled by the Board. Each is used for different kinds of projects, and different rules governing it\'s repayment\r\nC&D = Conservation & Development Fund\r\nCWL = Cities Water Loan Fund\r\nRCF = Revolving Construction Fund\r\n\r\nSecurity: Best guess for this field is that this field specifies the type of contract or agreement between the sponsor and the Board.\r\n\r\nStatus: The current status of the project and repayment to the Board\r\n\r\nAGMT NO: A unique identifier for the agreement.\r\n\r\nDATE: Date the agreement was made.\r\n\r\nSUBFUND: Identifier of the sub-fund funding was pulled from.\r\n\r\nAMOUNT $: Amount of money loaned or granted.\r\n\r\nDESCRIPTION: A short description of what infrastructure was built or repaired using the funds.\r\n\r\nTYPE PROJECT: What uses the infrastructure is to be used for.\r\nAGRICULTURE: Infrastructure was built for agricultural purposes.\r\nCULINARY: Infrastructure was built to provide culinary water services.\r\nSECONDARY: Infrastructure was built to provide secondary irrigation services.\r\n\r\nTYPE 2 PROJECT: Specifies if the project included multiple purposes.\r\n\r\nTYPE 3 PROJECT: Specifies if the project included multiple purposes.\r\n\r\nMANAGER: Name of the manager of the project. It looks like this is the Board staff that managed the project.\r\n\r\nRECEIVED: Date that the initial application was received by the Board.\r\n\r\nAUTHORIZED: Date that the detailed report (called a Feasibility Report) was reviewed by the Board in a meeting and formally authorized.\r\n\r\nCOMMITTED: Date that funds were officially committed to fund the project. This occurs at a formal sitting of the Board.\r\n\r\nTIN: I am not sure what this field is.\r\n\r\nFILE LOCATION: Specifies where the file is located. I do not know what the different entries mean.\r\n\r\nCONST COMPLETE: Date construction of the project was completed.\r\n\r\nRPMT COMPLETE: Date repayment of the project to the Board was completed.\r\n\r\nPROJ RETURNED: Not sure what this field means\r\n\r\nBOARD %: The percent of the total cost of the project that Board funds are paying for.\r\n\r\nBOARD $: The amount of money being loaned/granted by the Board.\r\n\r\nTOTAL $: The total cost of the project.\r\n\r\nAMD1 Date: The date that an amendment of the original agreement was made. This can be a change in the specifications of the project, a request for additional funds to cover unanticipated costs, or a request to change repayment terms.\r\n\r\nAMD1 Board $: Additional funds given by the Board.\r\n\r\nContinues through AMD8 Date and AMD8 Board $\r\n\r\nCOUNTY: The county in which the infrastructure is built.\r\n\r\nRIVER DISTRICT: The river district in which the infrastructure was built.\r\n\r\nDRAINAGE BASIN: The drainage basin in which the infrastructure was built.\r\n\r\nLOCATION: General location of the infrastructure. 9 NE MARYSVALE means 9 miles north-east of the Town of Marysvale.\r\n\r\nSEC: The section number (from the PLSS system: section township and range).\r\n\r\nTWP: The township number\r\n\r\nRNG: The range number\r\n\r\nB/M: Unknown\r\n\r\nINTEREST RATE %: The interest rate for the Board loan.\r\n\r\nRPMT TERM: The number of years of the repayment term.\r\n\r\nFIXED TRM TRUE: Are the payments fixed throughout the repayment term? True of False\r\n\r\n1ST RPMT DATE: Date that the first payment to the Board is due.\r\n\r\n1ST RPMT AMOUNT: Amount in dollars of the first payment.\r\n\r\nBOARD ADM FEE: Administration fee charged by the Board.\r\n\r\nWATER CONS PLAN (WCP): A water conservation plan is often required to be created by sponsors before the Board will award funds.\r\n\r\nWCP LOCATION: Unknown.\r\n\r\nPROJECT BENEFIT: The amount of money that will be generated as a direct benefit of the infrastructure. This is often realized in increased agricultural production.\r\n\r\nPROJECT COST: The amount of money the infrastructure will cost.\r\n\r\nB-C RATION: The benefit/cost ratio. Calculated from the previous 2 fields.\r\n\r\nAC-FT DEVELOPED: The amount of water (in acre-feet) of water conserved or developed by the proposed infrastructure.\r\n\r\nCOMMENTS: Comments made by Board Staff\r\n\r\nDSSG: Unknown\r\n\r\nDSSL: Unknown\r\n\r\nDSUG: Unknown\r\n\r\nDSUL: Unknown\r\n\r\nDS TOTAL: Unknown\r\n\r\nTYPE1: The type of infrastructure that is proposed\r\nCNL-REP = Canal Repair\r\nCL-SYST = Culinary System\r\nWELL-IRR = Irrigation Well\r\nDAM-ENL = Enlarge Dam\r\nCL - PIPE = Culinary Pipe\r\nTYPE2: \" \"\r\n\r\nContinues through TYPE4\r\n\r\nMISC: Miscellaneous notes\r\n\r\nENGINEER: The engineer or engineering company that designed the infrastructure.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWorksheet: 47-FY10\r\nThis worksheet is a simplified spreadsheet of the project, and is used to feed data in to the pivot table in the next worksheet. As it is, it contains projects from 1947 to the end of the 2010 fiscal year. This can be adjusted in order to get a pivot table that calculates for any given time period.\r\n\r\n\r\nWorksheet: pivot\r\nThis pivot table is designed to pull data from the 47-FY10 worksheet in order to compute total amount given by the Board, the total cost of projects supported by the Board, and the total number of projects supported by the Board in a given time period. In this case 1947 - 2010.\r\n');
