INSERT INTO `webform_submitted_data` (`nid`,`sid`,`cid`,`no`,`data`) VALUES (10,147,47,'0','Maps were digitized based on maps provided in the Board Folders. The maps provided by the Board were drawn over aerial imagery and sometimes USGS topo maps. In order to create spatially accurate digitized maps, USGS topo maps, AGRC NHD data, and .3 m satellite imagery (from the world imagery base map provided in ArcGIS) were used as background layers and references for where to draw the features. Infrastructure features were drawn using the editing tool based on best-available data from the background layers and the Board\'s map of the project. Satellite imagery was used as the primary template for a highly accurate location of features, especially for visible features such as canals or diversion structures. If there was not a sufficient view of a feature, then NHD data was used as the next best estimate for accurate spatial location of a feature. If neither of these references could be used to locate the feature, a best guess was made using the Board map. The scale of the Board provided maps was too coarse in most cases to get anything but the general vicinity of features, which could then be more accurately mapped using the other base maps. ');
INSERT INTO `webform_submitted_data` (`nid`,`sid`,`cid`,`no`,`data`) VALUES (10,147,48,'0','ArcMap 10.0 was the software in which the infrastructure features were digitized. ');
